(1056, 1, '2015-03-18 07:01:05', '2015-03-18 07:01:05', 'Omega Paints and Apco Coatings guarantee that products applied as per the specification and in accordance to the instructions will perform to the product expectations.\r\n\r\nAll Omega Paints and Apco Coatings products are manufactured at our fully accredited facility to ensure the highest quality of all coatings. Omega Paints and Apco Coatings technology come from local and international chemists and every batch is quality tested AT our on-site accredited laboratory before being released. This provides our customers with world-class products, in spec and in full every time.\r\n\r\nThrough its alliance with Asian Paints, Omega Paints and Apco Coatings has the benefit of accessing the largest research and development resource in the Asia-Pacific region.\r\n\r\nSince 1987, Omega Paints and  Apco Coatings, Australia has built a profound reputation in the Surface Coatings Industry. Omega Paints and Apco Coatings has always strived to engineer products to suit customer needs and has in its fold experienced laboratory technicians with advanced technology to cater to the customer requirements.\r\n\r\nTo be the best in Quality and Services in the manufacture of high quality coatings, catering to the needs of architectural coatings, industrial fabricators, equipment manufacturers, steel manufacturers, agricultural manufacturing and mining industries. Omega Paints and Apco Coatings manufactures and supplies high quality coatings to a host of residential, commercial and industrial clients as well as strives to deliver exceptional service and support to all customers at very competitive prices.\r\n\r\nAny Omega Paints and Apco CoatingS product that is properly maintained and regularly cleaned and then fails to preform to the product specifiation will be replaced free of charged for the affected area*\r\n\r\nThis guarantee only applies to Omega Paints and Apco Coatings products and excludes application over the breakdown of previously applied coatings. Coating failure caused by substrate faults, moisture ingress, surface contamination, corrosion, storm damage, mechanical damage, vandalism, coating additives and surfaces not prepared in a coating trade like standard as specified are not covered.\r\n\r\nClaims made for this guarantee must be made in writing to Omega Paints and Apco Coatings within 14 days of the fault being noticed. Proof of purchase must be included with any claim.\r\n\r\nThis guarantee does not limit and may not necessarily exceed your rights under the Competition and Consumer Act 2010.\r\n', 'Guarantee Policy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '978-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-18 07:01:05', '2015-03-18 07:01:05', '', 978, 'http://111.93.163.213/PaintOnline/php/978-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1057, 1, '2015-03-18 07:02:26', '2015-03-18 07:02:26', '<h2 style="text-align: center;">Despatch, Returns and Refunds Policy</h2>\n<strong>On Line Payment Options</strong>\n\nOn line payment are available by the following methods. PayPal, Visa and MasterCard. Bank transfer and cheque payments are acceptable and the order will be processed once funds as cleared in full. All amounts shown are in Australian Dollars (AUD).\n\n<strong>Dispatch and Delivery </strong>\n\nFree Delivery- Vic, NSW, Qld. Delivery charges applicable – SA, WA, NT and Tas. Please call 02 9832 0000.\n\nAll orders, after full payment received, will be dispatched from our warehouse within 2 business days for products in stock. Normal delivery is 3-4 business days after dispatch.\n\n(Western Australian and out laying areas may take longer). Delivery times are estimates only. If a product is out of stock, you will be contacted as to when the goods will be available.\n\n<strong>Returns</strong>\n\nAny goods to be returned must be re-saleable and the container unopened. All freight charges for returned stock are at the customer’s expense. Any returns must be accompanied with an issued credit number obtainable through our Customer Service department. Goods returned without a credit number will not be accepted. Tinted and made to order (MTO) goods are non-returnable. Returns must be completed within 30 days of sale invoice date. A 20% restock and handling fee will be charged on all returns.\n\n<strong>Refunds</strong>\n\nAny refundable monies will be credited via the method of payment received by the customer as per the sales invoice. We reserve the right to refund monies by whatever means are available. Dispatch, freight charges and handling are not refundable.\n\n<strong>Phone Orders</strong>\n\nYou may order by phone by calling Customer Service on (02) 9832 0000 weekdays between 8am to 5pm. (excludes public holidays).', 'Shipping Policy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '129-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-03-18 07:02:26', '2015-03-18 07:02:26', '', 129, 'http://111.93.163.213/PaintOnline/php/129-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
